                                                </div>
                                                <p>Sami joined the team at Johnny's Selected Seeds as the Territory
                                                    Sales Representative for Central and Southern California and Hawai'i
                                                    in 2022.</p>
                                                <p>Originally from Northern California, Sami found her way to
                                                    agriculture by following her passion for food. Upon completing her
                                                    Master's degree in Food Culture and Communications, she sought a
                                                    hands-on learning experience at a small-scale diversified farm.
                                                    After her first farmhand experience, she knew farming was something
                                                    worth dedicating her life to. In the years that followed, Sami
                                                    traveled around the States and Europe, working for various
                                                    small-scale vegetable operations, fruit farms, and vineyards.
                                                    Equipped with a background straddling the agriculture and wine
                                                    industries, having worked in both growing and sales, she now brings
                                                    these combined experiences and expertise to Johnny's.</p>
                                                <p>As a California grower, Sami is passionate about climate-resilient
                                                    farming practices that enhance soil health and water security. She
                                                    enjoys collaborating with many players to support and create
                                                    thriving regional food systems. She is excited to work with the
                                                    farmers in her territory to find the appropriate varieties and tools
                                                    to support their unique farming operations.</p>
