                                                    programs at Ohio State and Central State University, where she ran
                                                    training programs for beginning farmers in Ohio and provided
                                                    technical support for market gardeners.</p>
                                                <p>In 2019, Dana began her own 3-acre no-till farm outside of Columbus,
