                                            <div class="careertext">
                                                <div class="repimagequoteblock" style="margin-top: -15px;">
                                                    <div class="repimage"><img alt="Lauren Kendall"
                                                            src="{{ asset('front/on/demandware.static/-/Library-Sites-JSSSharedLibrary/default/dw7b8db5d2/images/landers/1hubpages/shop/commercial-sales/lkendall-300x400.jpg') }}"
                                                            width="300" height="400" loading="lazy" />
                                                        <div class="repimagecaption"
                                                            style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #567632;">Lauren Kendall
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="repquote"
                                                        style="font-size: 0.9em; line-height: 1.5em; font-style: italic;">
                                                        <span class="qmark">&ldquo;&nbsp;</span>Season after season, I
                                                        continue to be in awe of the seeds I sow; their processes of
                                                        coming to fruition never cease to amaze me! The deep respect and
                                                        honor I have for the seeds I also have for all the different
                                                        types of growers who work with them. It is a true pleasure to
                                                        support this relationship between growers and the seeds.<span
                                                            class="qmark">&nbsp;&rdquo;</span>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                                <p>Lauren has joined the team at Johnny's as the Mid-Atlantic,
                                                    Tennessee, and Kentucky Sales Representative.</p>
                                                <p>Lauren grew up gardening with her father in their home garden in
                                                    Coshocton, Ohio. She attended Denison University and double-majored
                                                    in International Relations and German. After graduation, Lauren
                                                    served in the Peace Corps in Mitsinjo, Madagascar, where she first
                                                    began to understand the importance of women, farming, health, and
                                                    the power of seeds.</p>
                                                <p>She determined then she would pursue this passion and curiosity, and
                                                    has been farming ever since. After WWOOFing in Argentina and
                                                    California she landed her first job as a farm assistant at Heirloom
                                                    Harvest in Massachusetts. She then went West to pursue a Montessori
                                                    model of goat farming and vegetable production for middle school
                                                    students in Santa Fe, New Mexico, where she met, married, and began
                                                    farming in tandem with her chef husband.</p>
                                                <p>The couple then moved to SingleThread Farms in Healdsburg,
                                                    California, where he worked in the kitchen and she managed the farm.
                                                    They next spent time in Big Sur, California in a similar farmer-chef
                                                    relationship, and moved to Tennessee in the middle of 2020, where
                                                    Lauren managed a 20-acre organic CSA farm outside of Nashville.</p>
                                                Lauren is also a trained Hoshindo apitherapist as well as a certified
                                                Biodynamic Craniosacral Therapist. Her healing arts practice has
                                                developed in partnership with her growing practice.
                                                <p>Current Sales Territory<br />
                                                    <strong>Kentucky, West Virginia, Virginia, Delaware, Maryland,
                                                        Washington, D.C., and Tennessee</strong><br />
