                                                        <div class="repimagecaption"
                                                            style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #567632;">Brandon Haines
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="repquote"
                                                        style="font-size: 0.9em; line-height: 1.5em; font-style: italic;">
                                                        <span class="qmark">&ldquo;&nbsp;</span>I know firsthand how
                                                        hard farmers work to provide the highest quality crops for their
                                                        customers. I am here to work with you to achieve your farming
                                                        goals.<span class="qmark">&nbsp;&rdquo;</span>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                                <p>A native of Pennsylvania, Brandon followed his love of nature to
                                                    Sierra Nevada College and graduated with a bachelor's degree in
                                                    environmental science and ecology. While in school he worked for the
                                                    University of California, Davis, at their Lake Tahoe Environmental
                                                    Research Center, studying invasive species and water quality. After
                                                    graduation he spent time in AmeriCorps, building and maintaining
                                                    trails throughout Nevada. In 2012 he returned to his native
                                                    Pennsylvania to apprentice on a diversified organic vegetable farm.
                                                    Supplementing his on-farm education there with classes at Penn State
                                                    Extension, he was then hired as vegetable production manager at
                                                    another diversified farm. In 2016 he bought his own farm in the
                                                    Lehigh Valley, owning and operating it for three years before taking
                                                    on management of another local organic vegetable farm.</p>
                                                <p>Most recently Brandon has joined Johnny's as the Territory Sales
                                                    Representative in Pennsylvania and New Jersey. His education and
                                                    hands-on experience have prepared him well to help farmers find the
                                                    tools and varieties that work best for their unique growing
                                                    situations.</p>
