                                                Vermont, and Connecticut</div>
                                            <div class="careertext">
                                                <div class="repimagequoteblock">
                                                    <div class="repimage"><img alt="Emma Golonka"
                                                            src="{{ asset('front/on/demandware.static/-/Library-Sites-JSSSharedLibrary/default/dwa8ecec9c/images/landers/1hubpages/shop/commercial-sales/egolonka-300x400.jpg') }}"
                                                            width="300" height="400" loading="lazy" />
                                                        <div class="repimagecaption"
                                                            style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #567632;">Emma Golonka</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="repquote"
                                                        style="font-size: 0.9em; line-height: 1.5em; font-style: italic;">
                                                        <span class="qmark">&ldquo;&nbsp;</span>New England farmers are
                                                        a resilient, intelligent, and resourceful group of people, and I
                                                        am immensely grateful to be able to work with and learn from
                                                        them. I’m here to help farmers find the best products to suit
                                                        their individual needs, and I believe that this work will
                                                        inherently strengthen food systems in this region and serve to
                                                        maintain agricultural traditions.<span
                                                            class="qmark">&nbsp;&rdquo;</span>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                                <p>Emma grew up farming in Western Massachusetts and graduated from
                                                    UMass Amherst with a degree in Plant, Soil, and Insect Sciences,
                                                    with a concentration in sustainable horticulture. She most recently
                                                    managed her family's diversified produce farm.</p>
                                                <p>As a farmer and member of the agricultural community, Emma
                                                    understands the small details involved in selecting the right
                                                    varieties, and how individualized that process and its outcome can
                                                    be to different growers. She enjoys trialing new selections and
                                                    assessing their use in varied settings.</p>
                                                <p>Emma adds, "Through my work on my own family's farm I have learned
                                                    the most from running our own trials, selecting the best varieties
                                                    for our particular needs, and discovering what will taste best and
                                                    serve our customers best. I've enjoyed this not only because it is
                                                    fun and the variation in cultivars is endlessly fascinating, but
                                                    also because the pursuit of excellence reflects a commitment to
                                                    doing our best by the community we feed, employ, and thereby
                                                    strengthen. My goal is now to apply that mindset to my territory;
                                                    whereas my farm and my valley were my prior focus, all the farmers
                                                    and growers of Western New England are now my people. I feel a
                                                    strong sense of responsibility for the advice I give and the success
                                                    of individuals and food systems here. I can't quite believe my luck
                                                    in joining Johnny's to share in the common pursuit of service and
                                                    excellence."</p>
                                                <p>Current Sales Territory<br />
                                                    <strong>Massachusetts, Vermont, and Connecticut</strong><br />
