                                                    <div class="repquote"
                                                        style="font-size: 0.9em; line-height: 1.5em; font-style: italic;">
                                                        <span class="qmark">&ldquo;&nbsp;</span>Food provides a way for
                                                        people to show they care about each other, to tell stories, and
                                                        to find identity and connection. Food can serve as a creator of
                                                        livelihoods, community engagement and cohesion, and citizen
                                                        empowerment.<span class="qmark">&nbsp;&rdquo;</span>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                                <p>From the foothills of Virginia, Camille discovered her passion for
                                                    agriculture early on as an equestrian and a devoted member of 4H.
                                                    She obtained degrees in Agricultural Technology and Environmental
                                                    Horticulture from Virginia Tech, and practiced sustainable
                                                    agriculture at Virginia Tech's organic farm, which supplies fresh
                                                    produce directly to the university's dining services. In addition to
                                                    her studies, she assisted extension research in hydroponic systems
                                                    and in hops production. Her broad horticultural background also
                                                    includes diversified vegetable and small fruit production, community
                                                    garden coordination, and commercial landscape experience.</p>
                                                <p>A dedicated food justice advocate, Camille strives to serve her
                                                    community by helping to transform the ways in which food is grown,
                                                    transported, accessed, and consumed.</p>
