                                                John&nbsp;Bauer</div>
                                            <div class="repdesc" style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;">
                                                Territory&nbsp;Sales&nbsp;Representative&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;Central and
                                                Southern California</div>
                                            <div class="careertext">
                                                <div class="repimagequoteblock">
                                                    <div class="repimage">
                                                        <img alt="John Bauer"
                                                            src="{{ asset('front/on/demandware.static/-/Library-Sites-JSSSharedLibrary/default/dw506cf7a7/images/landers/1hubpages/shop/commercial-sales/jbauer-300x200.jpg') }}"
                                                            width="300" height="200" loading="lazy" />
                                                        <div class="repimagecaption"
                                                            style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #567632;">John Bauer</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="repquote"
                                                        style="font-size: 0.9em; line-height: 1.5em; font-style: italic;">
                                                        <span class="qmark">&ldquo;&nbsp;</span>In 1973, I was one of
                                                        Johnny's first customers, meeting with Rob Johnston in his
                                                        basement seed store in Acton, Massachusetts. Rob discussed my
                                                        primeval organic crop plan with me and made some great variety
                                                        and cultural recommendations. From those beginnings I farmed for
                                                        over 30 years, and Johnny's has thrived for nearly 50.<span
                                                            class="qmark">&nbsp;&rdquo;</span>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                                <p>John works for Johnny's as a general consultant, assisting Sami Weiss
                                                    in the Central and Southern California territory; working with
                                                    several Californian farmers on seed sales; and assisting Product
                                                    Development in assessing varieties for California and the greater
                                                    West Coast region.</p>
                                                <p>John has farmed on both coasts, starting in Southern New Hampshire
                                                    with a small organic market farm in 1973. John moved the farm to the
                                                    Connecticut Valley of Massachusetts in 1977 and built it to 250
                                                    acres of conventional and organic production by 1993. In 1994, John
                                                    took a year off to condense his acreage to certified-organic
                                                    production only. He joined Johnny's in Albion, Maine as Research
                                                    &amp; Seed Production director for that year.  He worked with Rob
                                                    Johnston that year on the development of 'Bright Lights' Swiss chard
                                                    and improved winter squash and pumpkin varieties.</p>
                                                <p>John returned to his farm in 1995 and farmed organically through the
                                                    1998 season. In 1999, he decided to sell the farm to Full Bloom
                                                    Market Gardens/Happy Valley Organics in Whately, Massachusetts and
                                                    move to California. He took the position of General Manager for
                                                    Lakeside Organic Gardens, Watsonville, California. Later, he joined
                                                    in a partnership with Stone Free Farms, Aromas, California, growing
                                                    salad mix and specialty vegetable crops. In October 2001, John
                                                    joined a Salinas seed company and became immersed in the seed
                                                    business, specializing in organic seed and NOP-compliant coating
                                                    trials. He was involved in trialing the first coated seeds that were
                                                    NOP-compliant and worked with seed technology companies in the
                                                    Salinas area on NOP-compliant priming of lettuce seed. He also
                                                    worked with seed technology companies developing NOP-compliant seed
                                                    treatments for improved soil disease resistance, better vigor, and
                                                    nutrient usage.</p>
                                                <p>In 2009, John brought his extensive experience to our Commercial
                                                    Sales Team.</p>
                                                <p>Current Sales Territory<br />
                                                    <strong>Southern and Central California</strong><br />
